dismissalComment.html: short and wide outside the off stump, van Schoor goes for the cut and gets a faint edge, Dravid makes no mistake, Yuvraj Singh strikes in his first over!

gone! flighted delivery on the middle, van Rooi comes down the track and has a wild swing at it, ball hits the bat and balloons up towards the extra-cover region, Dinesh Mongia gets under it and makes no mistake

dismissalText.commentary: Gavin Murgatroyd lbw b Harbhajan Singh 0 (6b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: duck! flighted delivery on the off stump line, Murgatroyd offers no shot thinking it will spin away, the ball straightens and goes on to hit the pad plumb in front of the wicket, five down five more to go

dismissalText.commentary: Deon Kotze c & b Mongia 27 (50b 1x4 1x6 53m) SR: 54

dismissalComment.html: tossed up and on the off, punched back at the bowler, Mongia takes the simple return catch! A second wicket for Mongia in his spell of 10 overs

dismissalText.commentary: Melt van Schoor c †Dravid b Yuvraj Singh 24 (61b 1x4 0x6 50m) SR: 39.34

dismissalComment.html: short and wide outside the off stump, van Schoor goes for the cut and gets a faint edge, Dravid makes no mistake, Yuvraj Singh strikes in his first over!

headshotImage.longCaption: Yuvraj Singh headshot

dismissalText.commentary: Burton van Rooi c Mongia b Yuvraj Singh 17 (31b 2x4 0x6 29m) SR: 54.83

dismissalComment.html: gone! flighted delivery on the middle, van Rooi comes down the track and has a wild swing at it, ball hits the bat and balloons up towards the extra-cover region, Dinesh Mongia gets under it and makes no mistake

dismissalText.commentary: Bjorn Kotze c †Dravid b Yuvraj Singh 3 (18b 0x4 0x6 28m) SR: 16.66

dismissalComment.html: short and wide outside the off stump, Kotze goes for the cut and gets a thick edge, Dravid does well to hold on to it, the umpire is not convinced and the third umpire is woken up, replays show the catch was taken clearly, Yuvraj gets his 3rd

dismissalText.commentary: Gerrie Snyman c Srinath b Yuvraj Singh 5 (6b 1x4 0x6 10m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: a wild swing and the ball goes high up towards the long-off region, Harbhajan calls for it and gets under it but the ball jumps up after hitting his hands, Srinath standing close by grabs it, it's all over!

notes: India's total is the highest innings total on this ground in ODIs (previous: 126/0 Sri Lanka v Bangladesh, 2002/03)
SR Tendulkar's score is the highest on this ground in ODIs (previous: 69* MS Attapattu, Sri Lanka v Bangladesh, 2002/03)
When SC Ganguly reach 80* he completed 500 runs in World Cups
SR Tendulkar's score is his highest in World Cups (previous: 140* v Kenya at Bristol, 1999)

milestones.description: Burger and Swanepoel's 15-run partnership is NAM's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 12 between Burger and Swanepoel
Deon Kotze and van Schoor's 51-run partnership is NAM's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 15 between Deon Kotze and Burger
Bjorn Kotze and van Rooi's 25-run partnership is NAM's highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 10 between van Schoor and Sarel Burger
van Vuuren has become the top wicket-taker for NAM in ODIs with 7 wickets, going past Gerrie Snyman's 5
Ganguly has broken the record for most sixes (134) in ODIs for IND, going past Tendulkar's 133
Burger has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (4) for NAM, going past Louis Burger

stories.title: Well-oiled Indian machine steamrolls Namibia
stories.summary: The instructions were carried out to the letter, as India first piled up a mammoth score - 311/2 - and then used spin to tighten the screws on an inexperienced Namibian side, skittling them for 130 and winning easily by 181 runs.

stories.title: Well-oiled Indian machine steamrolls Namibia
stories.summary: The instructions were carried out to the letter, as India first piled up a mammoth score - 311/2 - and then used spin to tighten the screws on an inexperienced Namibian side, skittling them for 130 and winning easily by 181 runs.
